tunnels.subtitle: Create secure, outbound-only connections from your infrastructure to Cloudflare without opening inbound ports.
tunnels.columns.name: Name
tunnels.emptyState.title: Get started with Cloudflare Tunnel
tunnels.emptyState.description: Securely connect your applications and services to Cloudflare's network without opening inbound ports. Tunnel creates outbound-only connections, perfect for web apps, APIs, and development servers.
tunnels.tutorials.title: Get started
tunnels.tutorials.subtitle: Common use cases and guides for Cloudflare Tunnel.
tunnels.tutorial.publicInternet.title: Publish web apps and APIs to the Internet
tunnels.tutorial.publicInternet.descript: Learn how to expose your HTTP applications to the public Internet through Cloudflare.
tunnels.tutorial.highAvailability.title: Deploy highly available replicas
tunnels.tutorial.highAvailability.descri: Set up multiple tunnel replicas for production-grade reliability and failover.
tunnels.tutorial.vpc.title: Connect Workers to private services
tunnels.tutorial.vpc.description: Enable Workers to communicate with services in your VPC using Cloudflare Tunnel.
tunnels.create.title: Create a Tunnel
tunnels.create.description: Start by creating a Tunnel to connect your private network to Cloudflare. Then, you will be able to create a VPC Service for each service in the private network in which your Tunnel is running.
tunnels.create.description.v2: Start by creating a Tunnel to connect HTTP web servers, SSH servers, remote desktops, and other protocols securely to Cloudflare.
tunnels.create.form.tunnelName.label: Tunnel name
tunnels.create.form.tunnelName.required: A unique name for your Tunnel
tunnels.create.form.tunnelName.tooltip: A unique name for your Tunnel that will appear in the Cloudflare dashboard and CLI tools.
tunnels.create.operatingSystem.label: Operating System
tunnels.create.operatingSystem.setupDesc: Choose your operating system to get installation instructions.
tunnels.create.operatingSystem.tooltip: Select the operating system where you'll install and run the cloudflared daemon.
tunnels.create.architecture.label: Architecture
tunnels.create.architecture.tooltip: Select the CPU architecture of your system. Most modern systems use 64-bit architecture.
tunnels.create.installation.title: Install and Run
tunnels.create.installation.description: Run the following commands to install and connect your Tunnel.
